{
  "folder": "wSeYj7YJ85CRRgnP",
  "name": "Hijack Shadow",
  "type": "feat",
  "_id": "Z1WevTWQhrRwwyp8",
  "img": "icons/creatures/magical/humanoid-silhouette-dashing-blue.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Bonus Action</strong> - 1 Creature (5 ft.) - 10 Minutes - @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.IXk7hfrAoVQU3dLJ]{2 Ki Points} - Magical</p><p>You can now use &amp;reference[hide] inside a creature of small size or larger's shadow, merging with the shadows on the ground.</p><ul><li><p>When you do, you turn &amp;reference[invisible] then roll stealth (with advantage) to hide in the target's space.</p></li><li><p>You can be targeted by attacks and abilities (including by the hijacked target) as if in the same space as your target.</p></li><li><p>If you successfully used stealth to hide and you haven't given away your presence, the hijacked target usually won't know you're there.</p></li><li><p>If you end your turn and have not moved away from your target, you remain in the target's shadow, moving with them when they move on their turn. You remain invisible and occupy their space until this effect ends.</p></li><li><p>If you move away from your target, this effect ends.</p></li><li><p>If you roll an attack roll or cast a spell, then this ability will end when your turn ends.</p></li><li><p>When this ability ends, you appear in a space of your choice within 5 ft. of your target.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>While you can use this ability in darkness, if the target somehow doesn't cast a shadow or emits light, you cannot use this ability, and this ability ends if your target no longer cast a shadow or begins emitting light.</em></p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
